title: For Sale:  Walther PP
postcontent: Here is an excellent piece of WWII history. This pistol is a Walther PP in 7.65mm (or .32ACP) that was manufactured in March of 1945 and is "ac" stamped. It has the beech wood grips and does show some wear. This pistol was either a hastily assembled pistol at the end of the war or a GI assembled souvenir. It does have mismatched s/n numbers however both are in the March of '45 range. This is a very attractive pistol for its age and for when it was made.  Everything is tight, like it should be, and you can easily appreciate the German craftsmanship utilized to create this pistol at a time where the world was crumbling around Germany, which was quite an accomplishment.  Don't miss this chance to add a remarkable pistol to your safe and have an unusual piece of history that you can actually shoot.

title: For Sale:  SOLD: Zastava Mauser in .308 W/  Scope- Beautiful Rifle!
postcontent: SOLD: Here's a unique offering. I am pleased to offer this Zastava Arms M70 Mauser bolt-action rifle in .308 or 7.62x51mm NATO made in 2011. It has only had about 30 rounds fired through it. This rifle is in outstanding condition and in about 98% new condition with no wear or cosmetic issues to declare. This is the same action as the reknown German Mauser and it is made in the Zastava factory where they have been making Mausers since before WWII. This rifle's Mauser action is identical to the Remington 798, Parker-Hale 1200, Charles Daly and Interams Mark X. Zastava actually manufactured the receivers and bolts for ALL of those rifles. Typical Mauser features include a claw extractor on the bolt, a recoil lug that is machined into receiver body, controlled feed and a milled and deeply blued hinged floorplate on a 1 piece milled steel trigger guard/ magazine bottom plate. This rifle has high gloss bluing  the likes of which most rifle makers simply don't do anymore and if they do, it's expensive. Think Winchester M70 Super Grade; that's how nice this rifle's finish is. It also has a an equally attractive walnut stock with beautiful figuring in the wood grain, a classic European design, deluxe cut-checkering (not stamped!), a satin finish, low-profile right hand cheekpiece and a schnabel fore grip. The barrel is made of chrome-vanadium steel and is cold hammer forged providing greater steel density and hardness for consistant accuracy and lifelong durability. The trigger is excellent and fully adjustable as well. The scope in the pictures is not included but the Leupold Scope mount is and I will throw in a NC Star 4-16x50 Mil-Dot scope. Finally, I have mounted a leather rifle sling that is in keeping with this classic bolt-action Mauser. I am not interested in trades and my price is firm. For this rifle set up the way it is, this is a great deal! I will be happy to e-mail better and more pictures of the rifle for the serious would be buyer. If this ad is up on Armslist the rifle is available,

postcontent: NFA ITEM!KNIGHT'S ARMAMENT SR-15 E3 SBR MOD2, 14.5"The Knight's Armament SR-15 IWS E3 Mod 2 SBR may be based on the Eugene Stoner designed operating system but the similarities nearly end there.Features include a 14.5 inch chrome lined, 5.56mm NATO barrel that is manufactured to military specifications. Attached to the muzzle is the Knight's Armament 3 prong flash hider. New on the Mod 2 is a proprietary mid-length gas system that increases reliability and durability while also reducing felt recoil. The gas block no longer uses taper pins or set screws but is held on by a castle nut which allows for an air tight seal. Keeping with the air tight theme, the unique gas tube uses a compression fitting where it meets the gas block. This is very similar to what is used in automotive hydraulic brake lines. With these two features you won't have to worry about gas system leakage which can cause malfunctions, especially with lower powered ammo.On the opposite end of the barrel is Knight's Armament's proven E3 round-lug bolt which both enhances function and increases bolt life far beyond the industry standard. The bolt is desigend to outlive the barrel. The E3 bolt rides in a full auto carrier.Surrounding the barrel is Knight's new URX 4 keymod handguard, 13 inches in length. The extended length handguard allows for a forward grip which makes moving from target to target much faster. The keymod handguard will accept all standard keymod accessories such as hand stops, rail covers, light mounts or picatinny rail sections. One 5 slot picatinny keymod rail section is supplied with the rifle. The URX 4 handguard design increases cooling characteristics and reduces weight and bulk compared with standard 1913 rail attachment methods.An ambidextrous bolt release, selector, and magazine release offer left-handed users the ergonomic advantages inherent to AR15-based controls, as well as giving right-handed users alternative methods of manipulation to increase efficiency of movement. The drop-in two-stage trigger serves double duty as an aid to long range precision marksmanship while enabling surgical speed shooting at close range. Included parts and features, such as the two-sided receiver end plate QD sling swivel mounting point, collapsible six-position SOPMOD stock, hybrid ambidextrous selector lever, and folding 200-600 meter sights, round out the package to deliver a cutting-edge carbine right out of the case.*NFA rules apply, must ship to an FFL dealer with an SOT.$200.00 tax stamp to ATF. *Included:Knight's Armament SR-15 E3 14.5" SBR Rifle(7) Keymod rail panels, blackGI aluminum 30 round magazine with Knight's Armament follower (where legal)5 slot picatinny keymod rail sectionKnight's Armament logoed padded hard case(2) KAC QD sling swivelsMagwell block with lockOwner's manual
